<p><b>Tsutomu Miyazaki</b> <span style="font-weight: normal">(<span class="t_nihongo_kanji"><span lang="ja" xml:lang="ja">宮﨑 勤</span></span> <span class="t_nihongo_comma" style="display:none">,</span><i><span class="t_nihongo_romaji"><i>Miyazaki Tsutomu</i></span></i><span class="t_nihongo_help noprint"><sup><a href="/wiki/Help:Japanese" title="Help:Japanese"><span class="t_nihongo_icon" style="color: #00e; font: bold 80% sans-serif; text-decoration: none; padding: 0 .1em;">?</span></a></sup></span>, August 21, 1962–June 17, 2008)</span>, also known as <b>The <a href="/wiki/Otaku" title="Otaku">Otaku</a> Murderer</b>, <b>The Little Girl Murderer</b>, and <b>Dracula</b><sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since December 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup>, was a <a href="/wiki/Japanese_people" title="Japanese people">Japanese</a> <a href="/wiki/Serial_killer" title="Serial killer">serial killer</a>.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
